id: pm-r9ei
title: Fix Grafana RabbitMQ queue panel metric selector mismatch
description: "Telemetry overview dashboard queue panels query rabbitmq_queue_messages{queue=\"pm.telemetry.events\"} and rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked{queue=\"pm.telemetry.events\"}, but current Prometheus series on the remote stack have no queue label, so the panel query returns empty data despite non-zero queue depth."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[6]: external-audit,grafana,observability,pm-cli,prometheus,telemetry
created_at: "2026-04-26T09:56:16.564Z"
updated_at: "2026-04-27T19:45:21.965Z"
author: codex-agent
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: Grafana queue panels render live queue depth and unacked values in production by aligning panel queries with actual metric labels (or by exposing the queue label in exporter config).
parent: pm-lnq3
resolution: Grafana queue panel PromQL now uses job-scoped aggregates that match the RabbitMQ exporter label model on this stack.
expected_result: Queue depth and unacked panels evaluate successfully without relying on absent queue labels.
actual_result: "Dashboard expressions now use sum(rabbitmq_queue_messages{job=\"rabbitmq\"}) and sum(rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked{job=\"rabbitmq\"}); Prometheus returns non-empty vectors and Grafana remains healthy."
dependencies[1]{id,kind,created_at,author,source_kind}:
  pm-lnq3,parent,"2026-04-26T09:56:16.564Z",codex-agent,null
comments[8]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-26T09:56:16.564Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: pm context --limit 10; pm search 'Grafana rabbitmq queue dashboard metric label' --limit 10; pm search 'queue label rabbitmq_queue_messages' --limit 10; pm list-open --limit 20; pm list-in-progress --limit 20. Net-new because no open item currently tracks dashboard query label mismatch between Prometheus RabbitMQ series and Grafana queue panel selectors."
  "2026-04-26T09:57:02.619Z",codex-agent,"Remote evidence 2026-04-26: Prometheus query rabbitmq_queue_messages returns value 3 and rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked returns value 3, but both series are exported without queue label in metric metadata. Dashboard expressions filtering queue=pm.telemetry.events therefore return empty vectors and hide active queue backlog."
  "2026-04-26T13:16:13.794Z",cursor-agent,"Fresh remote audit evidence 2026-04-26: Prometheus query rabbitmq_queue_messages{queue=\"pm.telemetry.events\"} returned an empty vector, while unfiltered rabbitmq_queue_messages and rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked returned non-zero values without a queue label. Grafana/API/Prometheus were healthy, so the dashboard panel issue remains a selector-label mismatch."
  "2026-04-27T19:27:48.607Z",codex-agent,"Wave kickoff 2026-04-27: baseline captured via pm context/list-open telemetry snapshot; item remains in_progress under codex-agent. Next steps: inspect live Prometheus label model, compare Grafana queue panel queries, choose fix strategy from stack evidence, and verify queue depth panels render non-empty vectors after patch. Evidence logs linked under scripts/prod/telemetry baseline and pm-r9ei execution log."
  "2026-04-27T19:29:26.780Z",codex-agent,"Remote baseline 2026-04-27: Caddy host mappings are enabled for pm.unbrained.dev->:13000 and pm-cli.unbrained.dev->:18080. RabbitMQ queue shows live backlog (5/5), but Prometheus instant queries rabbitmq_queue_messages, rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked, and rabbitmq_queue_messages{queue=pm.telemetry.events} all return empty vectors, matching dashboard panel blank-state symptoms. Detailed evidence captured in scripts/prod/telemetry/2026-04-27-backlog-wave-baseline.md and scripts/prod/telemetry/2026-04-27-pm-r9ei-execution-log.md."
  "2026-04-27T19:38:54.416Z",codex-agent,"Implementation 2026-04-27: inspected live dashboard JSON and confirmed queue panel expressions in /home/steve/container/pm-cli/grafana/dashboards/pm-cli-telemetry-overview.json. Applied query hardening to explicit job-scoped aggregates: sum(rabbitmq_queue_messages{job=\"rabbitmq\"}) and sum(rabbitmq_queue_messages_unacked{job=\"rabbitmq\"}), then restarted grafana service to reload provisioning."
  "2026-04-27T19:38:57.283Z",codex-agent,"Verification 2026-04-27: Prometheus now returns non-empty vectors for the patched expressions (scalar vector values present), filtered queue-label query remains empty as expected for this exporter profile, dashboard JSON reflects patched expressions, and Grafana health endpoint stays database=ok."
  "2026-04-27T19:44:40.758Z",codex-agent,"Final evidence 2026-04-27: Prometheus query sum(rabbitmq_queue_messages{job=\"rabbitmq\"}) returns a non-empty vector and queue depth panel expressions in dashboard JSON match that label model; Grafana API health remains database=ok."
notes[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T19:29:32.022Z",codex-agent,"Fix strategy gate: inspect live Grafana dashboard JSON first, then patch query expressions to match actual exported RabbitMQ series labels unless exporter-level label restoration is clearly lower-risk."
  "2026-04-27T19:39:00.791Z",codex-agent,"Root cause is label-model mismatch: RabbitMQ exporter emits queue gauges with instance/job labels in this profile, not queue label selectors, so panel queries should aggregate over job-scoped series."
learnings[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-27T19:39:04.640Z",codex-agent,"For host-level diagnostics on this stack, use Prometheus published port 19090 (not container-internal 9090) to avoid false-negative query conclusions during dashboard triage."
